review_blob: Bottle. Pours clear, but dark brown color with a smallish light tan head on there. Nose first hits you with some caramel, then comes the whiskey; there is some underlying dark fruits in there, but actually seems like it would be sweet. Taste is definitely tart, but not as tart as you might think based on the nose. Hints of cherry and caramel on the back end.
Bottle. This one seems to have quite a bit of bith grains and citrus to it, almost like lemongrass. Slightly bitter and a bit heavy.
Bottle from the mix pack. Nose has some nice mix of spice and hops to it. Taste is bitter, but has some nice crispness to it.

Bottle. Really a nice citrusy IPA thats easy to drink. Nose is heavy on the citrus (notably tangerine) with just a bit of resin underneath. Taste is fairly bitter, but easy to drink and with a crisp finish. Solid brew.

Bottle. Pours a clear amber color with a moderate off -white head on there. Nose is quite hop forward, as youd expect, with some nice floral and grassy notes to it. Taste is rather bitter up front, but finishes pretty sweet, to the point where youd describe it as sticky.

Bottle. Pours a very clear amber color with a moderate off-white head on there. Nose really really pleasantly hoppy, with just hints of earthiness complementing a mix of resin and floral notes to it. Taste is moderately bitter, and quite tasty, with a fresh crisp finish. Very solid brew.
Bottle. Pours a near black color with a moderate tan head on there. Nose has dry roasty notes and some nice nuttiness. Taste is dry and extremely roasty with a hint of chocolate. Good brew.

Bottle. Pours a mostly clear golden color with very little head on it. Nose has some dry apply notes, but doesnt have a lot of smoke or pumpkin coming through. Taste is moderately sweet with just a hint of smoke to it on the aftertaste. OK.
beer_name: Tieton Cider Works Smoked Pumpkin Cider

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a hazy amber color with very little head on it. Nose has some honey and floral notes to it. Taste is a little sweet, and almost bitter finish, like its a light IPA. Interesting.
beer_name: Rocky Coulee Fireweed Honey Blonde Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a mostly clear amber color with a moderate off-white head on there. Nose has a lot of citrus and fruit notes to it, and is very hop forward. Taste is slightly bitter, but fresh and very drinkable. Decent brew.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a slightly hazy amber color with a moderate light tan head on there. Nose is fruity, with some blueberries to it and just a hint of citrus underneath. Taste is slightly sweet up front with a bitter middle and a slightly sweet finish. Lots of blueberry throughout. Decent brew.
Bottle. Nose has some stale hop elements to it as well as some earthiness. Taste is bitter with a hint of sweetness in the finish. Meh.

Bottle. Pours a clear light amber color with a moderate off-white head on it. Smells a little stale, as its been sitting out in the heat and light of a Total Wine for months. Taste is earthy and stale, and again I blame the venue from which it was purchased. Too bad, as I normally like the style.

Draught. Pours a slightly hazy amber color with a moderate off-white head on there. Nose is definitely hop forward, but with the grapefruit coming through more subtly than the floral and citrus notes. Taste is bitter and very fresh. Very good brew.
beer_name: Mac and Jacks Ibis IPA - Grapefruit

review_blob: Draught. Pours a mostly clear amber color with a moderate offf-white head on there. Nose has some pine and floral notes. Taste is bitter and crisp, and doesnt drink as high ABV as it actually is. Good brew.
Draught. Pours a very hazy tannish golden color. Nose is mostly sour, but with only subtle hints of apricot. Taste is sour and feels crisp. Decent brew.
Bottle. Nose has a lot of hops and citrus and resin coming through on this one. Taste moderately bitter and fresh. Easy drink.

Bottle. Pours a near black color with a moderate light tan head on there. Nose is floral and resiny and hop forward, without much roasting. Taste is bitter and roasty and super fresh. Very light and satisfying brew.
Bottle. Nose has a lot of hops and resin coming through and really makes for an inviting brew. Taste is moderately bitter and fresh, and an easy drink. Solid.
Bottle. Nose is hop forward and pleasantly fresh, with floral and grassy notes giving way to some spice underneath. Taste is earthy and bitter, but fresh and inviting. Good brew.

Bottle. Pours a near black color with a moderate brown head on it. Nose is roasty and slightly sour with a bit of dark chocolate coming through. Taste is just a tad bitter, but a slightly sweet finish with chocolate. Pretty good beer, Id have to say.
Bottle. Roasty and a little bit bitter. Very dry, but drinkable. Love it when you find new things at costco.

Bottle. Pours a near black color with a moderate light brown head on there. Nose is very roasty with a bit of vanilla and a bit of booziness to it. Taste is quite heavy on the vanilla and seems quite heavy on the alcohol. Decent.
beer_name: Avery Vanilla Bean Stout - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Bottle from the mix pack. Pours a very dark brown color with a moderate off white head on there. Nose is roasty and with a hint of toffee. Taste is ok, slight roasty bitterness to it.

Bottle from a mix pack. Pours a near black color with a moderate light brown head on it. Nose is heavy on the grains and reminds me of oats, but has little roasting to it. A little sourness to the nose as well. Taste is a bit roasty and slightly bitter, and feels remarkably light. Not sure what I think of this...
Bottle. Pours a very hazy amber color with a moderate light tan head on there. Nose has some nice light citrus notes to it. Taste is fairly fresh and moderately bitter. Decently nice and easy drink.

Bottle. Pours a hazy dark golden color without much head to it. Nose seems a little peppery to me, but I dont get habanero specifically (one of my favorite peppers), pineapple at all, or anything that would suggest a sour beer. Taste is offensively inoffensive, in that it tastes like beer, but nothing else - no heat, no actual flavoring, just boredom. Why?

Ok. So Ive had a shitty day on top of a super shitty week, and its not going to get any better. I wanted to drink a ridiculous amount of beer, but I didnt want to spend much money. Stopped into the RiteAid of all places, and this was on sale and a new tick. Justified enough. 

The beer sucks, by the way.

Bottle. Pours a very dark brown color with a moderate brown head on there. Nose is quite roasty with a bit of chocolate and a hint of oats. Taste is sweet and roasty with hints of cocoa. Really tasty and smooth.
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: Bitter Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a hazy light amber color without much head on it. Nose is stale, like all the hop character has gone (and bottled on 4/22/15 kinda confirms that). Taste is bitter up front with some residual sweetness. Would have like to try this fresh.

Bottle. Pours a rather hazy dark amber color with a lot of floaties and a small head on it. Nose is heavy on the rum and sugar, but with a fair amount of pumpkin coming through as well. Taste is sweet and quite a bit boozy, but with a nice bit of spice coming through. Im not a fan of rum or pumpkin, per se, but I like this a lot more than I expected to.

Bottle. Pours a mostly clear amber color with a smallish white head on there. Nose is subtle, but has some really nice floral and fruity elements to it. Taste is moderately bitter and fairly light, but doesnt come off too crisp or fresh. Decent, though.
Draught. Pours a dark golden color with a moderate white head on there. Very floral and slightly sweet nose, and just a hint of funk. Slightly sour and funky, but easy to drink. Nice.
Draught. Pours a dark brown color with a small head on it. Nose has a lot of dry dark roast coffee and little else. Taste is dry and bitter and heavy on the coffee. Decent brew.
beer_name: Two Beers Cold Brew Coffee Brown Ale

review_blob: Draught. Very floral and inviting hops to the nose on this one. Bitter taste, yet super smooth and clean. Nice brew.
Pours a rather dark brown with a moderate tan head on there. Nose is bitter and roasty with a hint of mocha. Taste is intense with coffee and roasting but light on the palate. Good brew.
beer_name: Mad River Kick Start Imperial Porter

review_blob: 22 oz. bottle. Wow. With the caveat that I DETEST coconut, I must confess that I hate this beer. Because it is very coconutty, and I hate coconut. My wife is drinking all but the tiny sip I took. Blech.

beer_brewer_name: The Traveler Beer Company (formerly House Of Shandy)
review_blob: Oy. My wife got this. Sweet and pumpkiny, but not enough spice to really draw you in. Very much too awful.
Bottle from a mix pack. Nice mix of floral and resiny hops and smells super sticky. Taste is nice and bitter, but dry and crisp. Very solid brew.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Five Hop Experimental IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Nose is pretty sticky and resiny like some sticky Double IPA. Taste is pretty bitter and comes across quite effervescent. Not a lot of sweetness at the end. Decent.
Bottle. Not a ginger fan, but the ginger seemed to be muted on this, which I preferred. It was bitter and earthy, but just a little heavy for me. Meh.
Bottle. Pours a clear amber color with a moderate tan head. Nice dry citrusy hop elements with a bit of a resiny backbone. Taste is moderately bitter, and with a nice crisp spicy bite. Solid brew.

Can from the advent calendar. Pours a clear golden color with a moderate white head on there. Smells of corn and yeast, with a little skunky lager bit to it. Taste is a little sweet, but tastes old and like nothing special.
Draught. Pours a pale amber color with a moderate off white head. Light floral hoppy nose. Taste is very light, slightly bitter, and really easy to drink.
Draught. Pours a hazy brown color with a moderate head on there. Nose is heavy on the resin and would pair well with pot. Taste is oddly sweet and not bitter enough.

Bottle. Pours a very hazy tan color with a huge thick off white head. Nose has some nice Belgian clove bits to it. Taste it a bit bitter with a slightly sweet finish. Very well aged beer. Quite happy.

Bottle from the Arrogant Bastard 4-pack of 22oz. Pours clear and dark brown with a moderate tan head. Nose has caramel and booze to it, with a subtle hint of coffee. Taste is bitter and a little grassy. Quite drinkable, all in all.
Can from the advent calendar. Nose has a lot of sweet caramel and bread to it. Taste is a bit sweet and heavy on the bread and yeast. Not a huge fan of this one.
If you mix Coors light and a gingerbread house, youll get this beer. Nothing about it is all that appealing.
Bottle. Nose has the notes of coffee and oatmeal you expect, but it seems to light to be a "real" stout. Taste has some coffee and a sweet finish, but is relatively forgettable.
